    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - CAB FEATURES - DIGITAL CLOCK PTC
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x0825821">
        <title>DIGITAL CLOCK PTC</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>CIRCUIT FUNCTIONS</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0825860">digital clock PTC function diagram</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0825860" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08258D1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
                <caption>Digital Clock PTC Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. VEHICLE BATTERY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CAB FUSE F12</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DIGITAL CLOCK PTC</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The digital clock PTC is generally used in applications where the optional entertainment radio is not
                installed on the vehicle.
            </para>
            <para>The digital clock PTC is power by battery voltage and is backlit by panel light dimmer voltage from
                the Gauge cluster.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
